00:00:00.670 --> 00:00:04.040
If you want to design a program, you might want to know first what

00:00:04.040 --> 00:00:08.250
the program is supposed to do. These instructions are called specifications and

00:00:08.250 --> 00:00:10.670
they might come from the customer, the end user or

00:00:10.670 --> 00:00:14.740
the analyst team. They might pr, provide it to you in informal text,

00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:18.880
in a structured document, or using a formal mathematical notation.

00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:23.250
This lesson focuses on precise specification using mathematical notations

